<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>↔️ Extra — CSS Flexbox Layout</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Flex Container, Direction &amp; Spacing · <strong>Course:</strong> Extra Worksheet · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>One line — <code>display: flex</code> — turns a box into a <strong>flex container</strong>. The boxes inside it become <strong>flex items</strong> and line up in a row. Then you steer them: <code>justify-content</code> slides them along the row, <code>align-items</code> moves them up and down, and <code>gap</code> puts space between them. On paper you will read Flexbox, predict it, fix it, and explain it in your own words.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Keep these words handy: <strong>flex container</strong>, <strong>flex item</strong>, <strong>flex-direction</strong>, <strong>justify-content</strong>, <strong>align-items</strong>, <strong>gap</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each snippet. Write what you think the page will look like.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .container { display: flex; }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;box&quot;&gt;A&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;box&quot;&gt;B&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;box&quot;&gt;C&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Without <code>display: flex</code>, A, B and C stack one per line. With it, where do they go?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The same three boxes. What does <code>column</code> do to them?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Three boxes, one wide container. Where does the empty space go?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each snippet is broken. Read what it should do, then rewrite it so it works. Explain why the original was wrong.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — The boxes should sit side by side. They stay stacked.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">.container { flex; }
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> <code>flex</code> is the value. Something is missing in front of it.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — The boxes are in a row but squashed together. There should be 24px between them.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">.container {
  display: flex;
  gap 24px;
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> every property needs a <code>:</code> between it and its value.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — The three boxes should spread across the row. Nothing moves.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;box&quot; style=&quot;justify-content: space-between;&quot;&gt;A&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;box&quot;&gt;B&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;box&quot;&gt;C&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> <code>justify-content</code> is a rule for the <strong>container</strong>, not for one item.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Explain the Code 📖</h2>
<p>This is the centred toolbar from your lesson.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .toolbar {
    height: 90px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    background: #1f2937;
  }
  .btn {
    padding: 10px 18px;
    background: #f97316;
    color: white;
    border-radius: 6px;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;toolbar&quot;&gt;
  &lt;button class=&quot;btn&quot;&gt;Cut&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;button class=&quot;btn&quot;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;button class=&quot;btn&quot;&gt;Paste&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>
<table style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;max-width:460px;margin:16px auto;text-align:center;font-size:13px"><tr><td style="padding:10px 0"><strong>justify-content</strong> — moves items along this way ⟷</td></tr><tr><td style="background:#1f2937;padding:22px 12px"><table style="border-collapse:collapse;margin:0 auto"><tr><td style="background:#f97316;color:#fff;padding:8px 14px;border-radius:6px">Cut</td><td style="width:16px"></td><td style="background:#f97316;color:#fff;padding:8px 14px;border-radius:6px">Copy</td><td style="width:16px"></td><td style="background:#f97316;color:#fff;padding:8px 14px;border-radius:6px">Paste</td></tr></table><div style="color:#e5e7eb;margin-top:10px">↕ <strong style="color:#ffffff">align-items</strong> — moves items this way</div></td></tr><tr><td style="padding:8px 0;color:#6b7280">the gaps between the buttons = <strong>gap: 16px</strong></td></tr></table>

<p><strong>Which box is the flex container — <code>.toolbar</code> or <code>.btn</code>? How do you know?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong><code>justify-content: center</code> and <code>align-items: center</code> both say <code>center</code>. What is different about the two?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>If you deleted <code>gap: 16px</code>, what would change? What would stay the same?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

